   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Summary — What Step 3 fixed\n",
    "\n",
    "| Exposure | Fix | Where |\n",
    "|----------|-----|-------|\n",
    "| S1-01 — indirect prompt injection | System prompt trust hierarchy + `<file_content>` data envelope | `SYSTEM_PROMPT` constant + `execute_tool()` |\n",
    "\n",
    "## Limitations\n",
    "\n",
    "These are **model-side, text-based controls** — they reduce the probability\n",
    "of injection success but cannot guarantee it.  The correct mental model is:\n",
    "\n",
    "> \"An injection that bypasses the system prompt can only cause harm\n",
    "> up to the limit of what the agent is allowed to do.\"\n",
    "\n",
    "That is why Steps 2 and 3 work together:\n",
    "- Step 2 (allowlist + budget) limits the agent's *capability*.\n",
    "- Step 3 (system prompt + envelope) limits the *likelihood* of exploitation.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Still open\n",
    "\n",
    "| Exposure | What's needed |\n",
    "|----------|---------------|\n",
    "| S1-06 — long-lived API key | Secrets manager / short-lived credentials |\n",
    "| S1-07 — secret redaction | Regex DLP pass on file contents before returning |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Step 4** will add secret redaction: a regex pass over file contents\n",
    "that replaces common secret patterns (API keys, passwords, tokens)\n",
    "with `[REDACTED]` before the contents ever reach the model."
   ]
  }
